General.Name: Red Hawk Mining Limited
General.Description: Red Hawk Mining Limited, an exploration and development company, focuses on its flagship asset, the Pilbara Iron Ore Project, which contains the Blacksmith mining lease and the Anvil retention license located in the Pilbara region of Western Australia. The company was formerly known as Flinders Mines Limited and changed its name to Red Hawk Mining Limited in July 2023. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in West Perth, Australia. Red Hawk Mining Limited is a subsidiary of Tio (NZ) Limited.
